						<summary>

						<p>On the eighth face of the fourth pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 28: 934-35 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 90 sheep by Śāttaṉ Tirumaṟaikkāḍaṉ, headman of Pālpulam for burning a perpetual lamp to the deity Tirumaṟaikkāṭṭu Āḷvār, with one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily by the measure called <hi rend="italic">Tirumaṟaikkāḍaṉ.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
